The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has explained the reasons many insurance firms fall short of quality financial statements.
  
The IMF highlighted this in a report entitled: ‘Publication of Financial Industry Assessment Program Documentation – Detailed Assessment of Observance of Insurance Core Principles’, stated that the challenge does not only hinder effective supervision but also timely disclosure of information to policyholders and the market.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .